{"lemma":"شُجاعٌ","slug":"شُجاعٌ","root":"ش.ج.ع","root_slug":"ش-ج-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ج-ع","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21766","n21767","n21768"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8F%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"brave, courageous, plucky, bold"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃu.d͡ʒaːʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21766","headword_ar":"شَجَاعٌ","root":"$jE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21767","headword_ar":"شُجَاعٌ","root":"$jE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaAEN","text_ar":"شِجَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, ISk, S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajaAEN","text_ar":"شَجَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) which is of the dial, of Benoo- 'Okeyl, being made by them to accord with its contr., which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabaAnN","text_ar":"جَبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiyEN","text_ar":"شَجِيعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaEu","text_ar":"اَشْجَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiEN","text_ar":"شَجِعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaEN","text_ar":"شِجَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in some copies of the K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaEapN","text_ar":"شِجَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in other copies of the K and in the TA,) [of all which forms the first is the most common,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Courageous, brave, valiant, bold, daring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong-hearted"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the occasion of war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making light of wars, by reason of boldness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) fem. [of the 1st and 2nd and 3rd respectively]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujaAEapN","text_ar":"شُجَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaAEapN","text_ar":"شِجَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, * K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajaAEapN","text_ar":"شَجَاعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, * K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$jAE","text_ar":"شجاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"also [without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Msb) and [of the 4th] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiyEapN","text_ar":"شَجِيعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and [of the 5th] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajoEaA='u","text_ar":"شَجْعَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of the 6th] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiEapN","text_ar":"شَجِعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) pl. masc. (of the 1st, S, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijoEapN","text_ar":"شِجْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] (AO, S, Msb, K) and [of the first three, and perhaps of the 4th also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajaEapN","text_ar":"شَجَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and (of the 1st, S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijoEaAnN","text_ar":"شِجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, S, K) and (of the 4th, S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujoEaAnN","text_ar":"شُجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, ISk, S, K) [or, accord. to IDrd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$jEAn","text_ar":"شجعان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a mistake, as is said in the TA, but the word is there written without any syll. signs,] and (of the 4th, S, Msb) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujaEaA='u","text_ar":"شُجَعَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and [of the 4th, and perhaps of others also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaAEN","text_ar":"شِجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and also, (but these are quasi-pl. ns., TA,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajoEapN","text_ar":"شَجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujoEapN","text_ar":"شُجْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajaEaA='u","text_ar":"شَجَعَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaEaA='u","text_ar":"شِجَعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajoEaA='u","text_ar":"شَجْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) pl. fem. [all of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiyEapN","text_ar":"شَجِيعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or the last of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajoEaA='u","text_ar":"شَجْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiEapN","text_ar":"شَجِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajaAy^iEu","text_ar":"شَجَايِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaAEN","text_ar":"شِجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujuEN","text_ar":"شُجُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lh, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujaAEN","text_ar":"شُجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [an epithet] peculiar to men: (K, * TA:) AZ says, “ I have heard the Kilábees say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN $ujaAEN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ شُجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but they do not apply this epithet to a woman: ” (S:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiEapN","text_ar":"شَجِعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiyEapN","text_ar":"شَجِيعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", however, are applied to a woman, and signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"longtongued, and vehemently clamorous, towards men;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"audacious in her speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn- 'Abbád, K, [but these two epithets as applied to a woman and signifying “ bold ” &c. are omitted in the CK,])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in her length of tongue, and vehement clamorousness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujaAEN","text_ar":"شُجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijaAEN","text_ar":"شِجَاعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) also signify (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serpent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and so does ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaEu","text_ar":"اَشْجَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or (tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male serpent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain species of serpent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, S, Msb, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaEu","text_ar":"اَشْجَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slender, and asserted to be the boldest of the serpent-kind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ijoEaAnN","text_ar":"شِجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, IDrd, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujoEaAnN","text_ar":"شُجْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, K,) the former of which is the more common: (IDrd:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaEu","text_ar":"اَشْجَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aAjiEu","text_ar":"اَشَاجِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, as some say, this is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojiEapN","text_ar":"اَشْجِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is pl. [of pauc.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$jAE","text_ar":"شجاع"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serpent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajoEamN","text_ar":"شَجْعَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", above.] ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serpent called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SafarN","text_ar":"صَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that presents itself in the belly"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as the Arabs assert,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when he has been long hungry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) but As says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujaAEu AlbaToni","text_ar":"شُجَاعُ البَطْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence of hunger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Lh","ISk","S","Msb","K","AO","TA","Mgh","Sh","IDrd"]},{"entry_id":"n21768","headword_ar":"شِجَاعٌ","root":"$jE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujaAEN","text_ar":"شُجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}